@NODE INTRO "An introduction"

1. An introduction
==================

     OK, let's face it, most of us use Windows machines at work or even at
     home to surf the net. But... this will not keep me from using my Amiga
     to surf the net too.

     HotFavBook will convert your Windows XP or Windows 2000 'Favorites' to
     an IBrowse hotlist file. This allows you to build a big library of nice
     sites and to regularly convert this list to your Amiga.  

     Only a conversion from Windows Favorites to an IBrowse hotlist is 
     supported. If you need another format please use BookCon (also on Aminet)
     to convert it. 

     This program is mailware. If you like/hate it let me know! 
     If I get enough response this will encourage me to develop it further!

     Feel free to contact me with any comments or questions.

@ENDNODE

@NODE USAGE "Usage"

2. Usage
========

     HotFavBook runs from WorkBench only and the use of it is pretty straight-
     forward. Select a source (directory for Favorites) select a destination
     and hit the convert button.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CTRLS "Controls"

3. Controls
===========

     HotFavBook can be controlled by using the MUI gadgets. All default
     input parameters can be overriden by typing other values in the
     appropriate gadgets.
    
     The screen consists of two string gadgets in which you can type the
     the source directory and the destination file and 2 cycle gadgets which
     allow you to choose the source and destination type.
     
     There are three buttons: the Convert button starts the conversion proces,
     the About button shows the about screen with version info of the program
     and the Quit button quits the application.
     
     In the statusline at the bottom of the window appears any message or
     error that might have occurred.
     
     In the menu you can find items for convert, quit, about and content.

     Online help is available by pressing the Help key or selecting content
     from the Help menu.
     
@ENDNODE

